org.hawaiiframework.web.input

Interface InputConverter<S,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the input object
    T - the type of the domain object

    public interface InputConverter<S,T>
    Interface for components that convert input data into a domain object.

    The input should be a type that is only used in the REST layer of the application and which represents the data structure to be send by the consumer. This is typically a POJO containing Jackson annotations if needed.

    Since:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Wouter Eerdekens, Marcel Overdijk
